ntntechInterfaceModuleConfigurationMIB.name: ntntechInterfaceModuleConfigurationMIB

revisions.description: Added to the ifCfgPortTable the OID ifCfgPortBkBoneEtherType. VLAN ID max limit changed from 4095 to 4085.
Added fixedadaptive(4) mode to the ifCfgPortAdslPortMode OID.
Added to the comment section of ifCfgPortT1RxTxRate and ifCfgPortE1RxTxRate the newly supported T1/E1 module types - tim1500p12(31), tim1500p24(32), eim2000p12(33), eim2000p24(34)

ntntechInterfaceModuleConfigurationMIB.contactinfo: Paradyne Corporation 8545 126th Avenue North Largo, FL 33773 phone: +1 (727) 530-2000 email: support@paradyne.com www: http://www.nettonet.com/support/
ntntechInterfaceModuleConfigurationMIB.description: This mib module defines an SNMP API to manage Paradyne Corporation's IPD12000, IPD4000, and Mini/Micro DSLAM interface parameters. The interface types are described below, AMD8000-12 12-Port ADSL Mini DSLAMs With Full Rate and G.lite Operational Modes AAM8000-12 12-Port ADSL Access Multiplexer with Full Rate and G.lite Operational Modes AAM8000-24 24-Port ADSL Access Multiplexer with Full Rate and G.lite Operational Modes EAM2000-12 12-Port E1 Access Multiplexer TAM1500-12 12-Port T1 Access Multiplexer IAM144-12 12-Port IDSL Access Multiplexer SAM1000-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexer SAM2000-12, SAM2000Q-12, and SAM2000G-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexers with CAP, 2B1Q or TC/PAM (G.SHDSL) encoding SAM2000D-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexer W/O voice daughter card, running CAP encoding SAM2000DQ-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexer W/O voice daughter card, running 2B1Q encoding SAM2000V-12, SAM2000QV-12, SAM2000GV-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexers with Voice Capability running CAP, 2B1Q or TC/PAM (G.SHDSL) encoding SIM2000-12 12-Port SDSL Access Multiplexer with CAP, 2B1Q and TC/PAM (G.SHDSL) encoding SIM2000-24 24-Port SDSL Access Multiplexer with CAP, 2B1Q and TC/PAM (G.SHDSL) encoding SMD2000-12, SMD2000Q-12, SMD2000G-12 12-Port SDSL Mini DSLAMs: AC and DC Versions with Cap, 2B1Q and G.SHDSL Line encoding SuD2011_12T, SuD2011_12E, SuD2003_12T, SuD2003_12E 12-Port SDSL Micro DSLAMs: Cap, 2B1Q and G.SHDSL Line encoding SuD2011_6T, SuD2011_6E, SuD2002_6T, SuD2002_6E 6-Port SDSL Micro DSLAMs: Cap, 2B1Q and G.SHDSL Line encoding

ifCfgPortTable.name: ifCfgPortTable
ifCfgPortTable.description: A list of IPD12000, IPD4000 Access/Inverse module and Mini/Micro DSLAM entries.

ifCfgPortEntry.name: ifCfgPortEntry
ifCfgPortEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the IPD12000, IPD4000 Access/Inverse module as well as the Mini/Micro DSLAM.

ifCfgSlotIndex.name: ifCfgSlotIndex
ifCfgSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the IPD chassis to which the interface module resides. The Mini/Micro DSLAM will have a slot index value of 1.

ifCfgPortIndex.name: ifCfgPortIndex
ifCfgPortIndex.description: The physical port number of the interface.

ifCfgPortCircuitID.name: ifCfgPortCircuitID
ifCfgPortCircuitID.description: The circuit identification number assigned to a port on an interface.

ifCfgPortFltrIp1Start.name: ifCfgPortFltrIp1Start
ifCfgPortFltrIp1Start.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the start of the first Ip filter range.

ifCfgPortFltrIp1End.name: ifCfgPortFltrIp1End
ifCfgPortFltrIp1End.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the end of the first Ip filter range.

ifCfgPortFltrIp2Start.name: ifCfgPortFltrIp2Start
ifCfgPortFltrIp2Start.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the start of the second Ip filter range.

ifCfgPortFltrIp2End.name: ifCfgPortFltrIp2End
ifCfgPortFltrIp2End.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the end of the second Ip filter range.

ifCfgPortBackboneVlan.name: ifCfgPortBackboneVlan
ifCfgPortBackboneVlan.description: The Backbone VLAN tag will become the primary identifier that can be used by routers with backbone capabilities to direct traffic to the appropriate network cloud.

ifCfgPortVlanPriority.name: ifCfgPortVlanPriority
ifCfgPortVlanPriority.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the VLAN priority.

ifCfgPortFloodMde.name: ifCfgPortFloodMde
ifCfgPortFloodMde.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the flood mode.

ifCfgPortIpFltProtocol.name: ifCfgPortIpFltProtocol
ifCfgPortIpFltProtocol.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the IP filter protocol.

ifCfgPortReset.name: ifCfgPortReset
ifCfgPortReset.description: This value is always read as integer value 2. Reset all associated port statistics to zero upon initiation of the reset(1).

ifCfgPortBkBoneEthType.name: ifCfgPortBkBoneEthType
ifCfgPortBkBoneEthType.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the ethernet packet type.

ifCfgPortVLANTable.name: ifCfgPortVLANTable
ifCfgPortVLANTable.description: A list of IPD12000, IPD4000 Access/Inverse module and Mini/Micro DSLAM port 802.1Q VLAN entries.

ifCfgPortVLANEntry.name: ifCfgPortVLANEntry
ifCfgPortVLANEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to an IPD12000, IPD4000 Access/Inverse module and Mini/Micro DSLAM port.

ifCfgIfSlotIndex.name: ifCfgIfSlotIndex
ifCfgIfSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the IPD chassis to which the interface module resides. The Mini/Micro slot index will be 1.

ifCfgIfPortIndex.name: ifCfgIfPortIndex
ifCfgIfPortIndex.description: The physical port number of the interface.

ifCfgVLANIndex.name: ifCfgVLANIndex
ifCfgVLANIndex.description: A pointer to one of ten possible VLAN tags that can be assigned to a port.

ifCfgVLANIdStart.name: ifCfgVLANIdStart
ifCfgVLANIdStart.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the start of a VLAN ID range.

ifCfgVLANIdEnd.name: ifCfgVLANIdEnd
ifCfgVLANIdEnd.description: The value assigned to a port which designates the end of a VLAN ID range.

ifCfgPortAdslTable.name: ifCfgPortAdslTable
ifCfgPortAdslTable.description: A list of ADSL interface entries.

ifCfgPortAdslEntry.name: ifCfgPortAdslEntry
ifCfgPortAdslEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to ADSL module.

ifCfgAdslSlotIndex.name: ifCfgAdslSlotIndex
ifCfgAdslSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the IPD chassis to which the interface module resides. The Mini/Micro slot index will be 1.

ifCfgAdslPortIndex.name: ifCfgAdslPortIndex
ifCfgAdslPortIndex.description: The physical port number of the ADSL interface.

ifCfgPortAdslPortMode.name: ifCfgPortAdslPortMode
ifCfgPortAdslPortMode.description: The port mode of operation, ON, OFF, or Adaptive. When a port is set to Adaptive mode, the best possible value for the Rx/Tx data rates will be achieved. A successful data rate connection will be indicated with a port 'linkup' status.

ifCfgPortAdslVpiVciDetect.name: ifCfgPortAdslVpiVciDetect
ifCfgPortAdslVpiVciDetect.description: ADSL Virtual Path Identifier (VPI) and Virtual Channel Identifier (VCI) detect mode. If this mode is set to ON, auto-detect the line VPI and VCI values.

ifCfgPortAdslRxRate.name: ifCfgPortAdslRxRate
ifCfgPortAdslRxRate.description: ADSL upstream (Rx) data rate. The available upstream data rates range from 32Kbps to 1024Kbps. The upstream data rate can be set by the user via the set value x where x = 1 to 32. The actual data rate that is represented by these set values can be calculated using the following formula, (x * 32Kbps) = upstream data rate, i.e. (3 * 32Kbps) = 96Kbps Note: if an Rx rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, this would indicate that the port is in 'Adaptive' mode and that the link condition is 'linkdown'.

ifCfgPortAdslTxRate.name: ifCfgPortAdslTxRate
ifCfgPortAdslTxRate.description: ADSL downstream (Tx) data rates. The available downstream data rates range from 32Kbps to 8064Kbps. The downstream data rate can be set by the user via the set value x where x = 1 to 252. The actual data rate that is represented by these set values can be calculated using the following formula, (x * 32Kbps) = downstream data rate, i.e. (252 * 32Kbps) = 8064Kbps Note: if a Tx rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, this would indicate that the port is in 'Adaptive' mode and that the link condition is 'linkdown'.

ifCfgPortAdslStandardMde.name: ifCfgPortAdslStandardMde
ifCfgPortAdslStandardMde.description: ADSL standard modes of operation. Note: if receive a standard mode of integer value 255 (0xFF), this would indicate that the standard mode is unknown due to a port 'linkdown' condition.

ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionUp.name: ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionUp
ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionUp.description: ADSL Impulse protection duration in the Upstream duration.

ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionDn.name: ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionDn
ifCfgPortAdslCorrectionDn.description: ADSL Impulse protection duration in the Upstream duration.

ifCfgPortAdslDelayUp.name: ifCfgPortAdslDelayUp
ifCfgPortAdslDelayUp.description: ADSL Impulse protection duration in the Upstream direction.

ifCfgPortAdslDelayDn.name: ifCfgPortAdslDelayDn
ifCfgPortAdslDelayDn.description: ADSL Impulse protection duration in the Upstream direction.

ifCfgPortAdslEcFdm.name: ifCfgPortAdslEcFdm
ifCfgPortAdslEcFdm.description: ADSL Echo Cancellation uses Upstream Tones for Upstream and Dnstream data.

ifCfgPortAdslFastBuffer.name: ifCfgPortAdslFastBuffer
ifCfgPortAdslFastBuffer.description: Selects fast buffer/low latency. Same is interleave delay of 1ms

ifCfgPortAdslActualRxRate.name: ifCfgPortAdslActualRxRate
ifCfgPortAdslActualRxRate.description: ADSL upstream (Rx) data rate. The available upstream data rates range from 32Kbps to 1024Kbps. The upstream data rate can be set by the user via the set value x where x = 1 to 64. The actual data rate that is represented by these set values can be calculated using the following formula, (x * 32Kbps) = upstream data rate, i.e. (3 * 32Kbps) = 96Kbps Note: if an Rx rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, this would indicate that the port is in 'Adaptive' mode and that the link condition is 'linkdown'.

ifCfgPortAdslActualTxRate.name: ifCfgPortAdslActualTxRate
ifCfgPortAdslActualTxRate.description: ADSL downstream (Tx) data rates. The available downstream data rates range from 32Kbps to 8064Kbps. The downstream data rate can be set by the user via the set value x where x = 1 to 1024. The actual data rate that is represented by these set values can be calculated using the following formula, (x * 32Kbps) = downstream data rate, i.e. (252 * 32Kbps) = 8064Kbps Note: if a Tx rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, this would indicate that the port is in 'Adaptive' mode and that the link condition is 'linkdown'.

ifCfgPortAdslActualStandardMde.name: ifCfgPortAdslActualStandardMde
ifCfgPortAdslActualStandardMde.description: ADSL current operating mode, should match ifCfgPortAdslStandardMde UNLESS operating in MULTIMODE

ifCfgPortIdslTable.name: ifCfgPortIdslTable

ifCfgPortIdslEntry.name: ifCfgPortIdslEntry
ifCfgPortIdslEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to the IDSL interface.

ifCfgIdslSlotIndex.name: ifCfgIdslSlotIndex
ifCfgIdslSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the IPD chassis to which the interface module resides. The Mini/Micro slot index will be 1.

ifCfgIdslPortIndex.name: ifCfgIdslPortIndex
ifCfgIdslPortIndex.description: The physical port number of the IDSL interface.

ifCfgPortIdslRxTxRate.name: ifCfgPortIdslRxTxRate
ifCfgPortIdslRxTxRate.description: IDSL symetrical (Rx/Tx) data rates. IDSL module types and the associated Rx/Tx data rates- IAM144-12: Data Rates (Kbps): 128,144 Note: if a rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, it will indicate that the port is defective.

ifCfgPortSdslRxTxRate.name: ifCfgPortSdslRxTxRate
ifCfgPortSdslRxTxRate.description: SDSL symetrical (Rx/Tx) data rates. SDSL module types and the associated Rx/Tx data rates- SAM1000-12: Data Rates (Kbps): 272,528,784,1168 SAM2000-12,SAM2000Q-12,SAM2000G-12,SAM2000D-12,SAM2000DQ-12, SIM2000-24,SuD2011_12T,SuD2011_12E,SuD2003_12T,SuD2003_12E, SuD2011_6T,SuD2011_6E,SuD2002_6T,SuD2002_6E: Data Rates (Kbps): 144,272,400,528,784,1040,1552,2064,2320 SAM2000V-12,SAM2000QV-12,SAM2000GV-12,SIM2000V-12,SIM2000V-24: Data Rates (Kbps): 272,400,528,784,1040,1552,2064,2320 Note: if a rate value of zero(0) is returned via a GET operation, it will indicate that the port is defective.

ifCfgPortSdslLineCode.name: ifCfgPortSdslLineCode
ifCfgPortSdslLineCode.description: Line code for the SDSL modules. Note, the line code may be set on the following modules, SIM2000-12,SIM2000-24,SIM2000V-24,SIM2000V-12, or the SDSL micro DSLAM. The line code options are described as follows- CAP: Carrierless Amplitude and Phase modulation 2B1Q: Two Binary, One Quaternary G.SHDSL: Multirate Symmetric Single-pair DSL
